The paper discusses the design of color maps for data visualization, which is a core concept in computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of color maps in microscopies and spectroscopies, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also emphasizes the importance of perceptually uniform color spaces for improving data readability and interpretation, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
